## Log scores of win predictions

~~~{.R}
convert <- function(a) unlist(lapply(a, function(x) x/100))
logScore <- function (obs, pred) {Reduce("+", na.omit(unlist(Map(function (o,p) {
                                                                  if (o) {log(p)} else {log(1-p)} },
                                                                 convert(obs), convert(pred)))))}
~~~

Example of the difference between Brier and log score:

~~~{.R}
# Oops!
brier(0,1,bins=FALSE)$bs
1
# But we can recover by getting the second right
brier(c(0,1),c(1,1),bins=FALSE)$bs
0.5

# Oops!
logScore(1, 0)
-Inf
# Can we recover? ...we're screwed
logScore(c(1,1), c(0,100))
